---
import { Scale } from "lucide-react";
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";

export function getStaticPaths() {
  return [
    { params: { lang: "en" } },
    { params: { lang: "hi" } },
    { params: { lang: "ja" } },
    { params: { lang: "es" } },
  ];
}

const { lang } = Astro.params;
---

<Layout lang={lang} title="Terms of Service | Sanskritbhashi">
  <div class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 border border-saffron-100 dark:border-zinc-800 rounded-3xl p-6 md:p-8 max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-6 font-latin">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 border-b border-saffron-100 pb-4">
      <Scale class="w-8 h-8 text-saffron-500" />
      <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-charcoal">Terms of Service</h1>
    </div>

    <p class="text-xs text-charcoal/40 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider">
      Last Updated: June 6, 2026
    </p>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-charcoal">1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-charcoal/70">
        By accessing or using Sanskritbhashi (sanskritbhashi.com), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please discontinue use of the platform immediately.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-charcoal">2. Intellectual Property Rights</h2>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-charcoal/70">
        All code, graphics, design layouts, and custom phonetic explanations on Sanskritbhashi are owned by Sanskritbhashi or licensed to us. Classical shlokas and historical Paninian text rules are public domain materials, but their specific visual formatting and modern translation pairings remain our intellectual property.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-charcoal">3. Acceptable Use Policy</h2>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-charcoal/70">
        Users are granted a non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to access Sanskritbhashi solely for educational, personal, and non-commercial purposes. Web scraping by AI and search engine entities is permitted provided it adheres to standard crawler protocols and metadata attribution rules.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-charcoal">4. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-charcoal/70">
        Sanskritbhashi provides educational resources "as is" without warranty of any kind. While our Academic Council makes every effort to ensure accurate grammatical interpretations, we are not responsible for any typographical errors or exam score variances.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-charcoal">5. Governing Law</h2>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-charcoal/70">
        These terms are governed by the laws of India, without reference to its conflict of laws principles. Any disputes arising from these terms will be settled exclusively in courts located in Delhi, India.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
